      • createMissionInvite

        public void createMissionInvite(Map<String,Object> params,
                       ISirqulCallback<WrappedResponse<MissionResponse>> callback)
        Create the mission invite. An account can only be invited to a mission one time. For missions that require user submission and reviewing the permissionableType and permissionableId need to be provided.

        Target API Endpoint: /mission/invite/create

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required).
        • SirqulKeys.missionId
          The mission to find the invite for.
        • SirqulKeys.includeGameData
          the include game data

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        error SirqulResponse, success a WrappedResponse< MissionResponse>
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.

          the application version, used to version the game level data
        • SirqulKeys.missionId
          the mission id to filter on
        • SirqulKeys.status
          The invite status to filter for, comma separated list

          Only return invites that have been updated since this date/time (long)
        • SirqulKeys.start
          The index into the record set to start with.
        • SirqulKeys.limit
          The total number of record to return.
        • SirqulKeys.keyword
          The keyword to search on.
        • SirqulKeys.filterByBillable
          filter results by the account's billable
        • SirqulKeys.includeGameData
          Include the game level data with the mission.

        public void updateMissionInvite(Map<String,Object> params,
                       ISirqulCallback<WrappedResponse<MissionResponse>> callback)
        Update the mission invite status. An account can only be invited to a mission one time. For missions that require user submission and reviewing the permissionableType and permissionableId need to be provided.

        Target API Endpoint: /mission/invite/update

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId sent automatically).
        • SirqulKeys.missionId
          The mission to find the invite for (missionId or missionInviteId requried).
        • SirqulKeys.missionInviteId
          The mission invite id. This checks on the user's billable for permission (missionId or missionInviteId requried).
        • SirqulKeys.status
          The invite status to filter for, comma separated list
          {AVAILABLE, PENDING, UPDATED, ACCEPTED, ACTIVE, QUIT, COMPLETED, PENDING_REVIEW, REJECTED}
        • SirqulKeys.permissionableType
          The type of item being modified by the mission.
          {ACCOUNT, GAMELEVEL, COLLECTION, ALBUM_CONTEST, THEME_DESCRIPTOR, ALBUM}
        • SirqulKeys.permissionableId
          The id of the item being modified by the mission.
        • SirqulKeys.includeGameData
          Include the game level data with the mission.

        error SirqulResponse, success a WrappedResponse< MissionResponse>
